1
00:01:00,927 --> 00:01:04,954
Man: Trees have a secret life
that is only revealed

2
00:01:04,998 --> 00:01:06,966
to those who are willing
to climb them.

3
00:01:21,381 --> 00:01:23,474
I do not remember
when I was born.

4
00:01:24,617 --> 00:01:26,141
But, when I was three
months old,

5
00:01:26,186 --> 00:01:28,780
my mother returned
to my grandparents' home

6
00:01:28,822 --> 00:01:31,222
with me as the proof
of her failure.

7
00:01:53,313 --> 00:01:56,771
The splendor of my childhood
was unique,

8
00:01:57,550 --> 00:02:02,214
because of its absolute poverty,
and absolute freedom...

9
00:02:04,157 --> 00:02:05,886
out in the open,

10
00:02:05,925 --> 00:02:09,224
surrounded by trees,
animals, and people

11
00:02:09,262 --> 00:02:11,628
who were indifferent
toward me.

12
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:23,339
Grandmother: Reinaldo!

13
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:26,506
Reinaldo!

14
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:31,613
Niño, apúrate con esa agua,
Dios mío!

15
00:02:31,651 --> 00:02:33,585
Mira que hay que esperar
en esta casa!

16
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:37,249
My early life was surrounded
by a room full of unhappy women

17
00:02:37,290 --> 00:02:40,726
who were all bossed around
by my grandmother,

18
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:43,752
the heart of the house,

19
00:02:43,796 --> 00:02:46,731
the only woman I ever saw
who peed standing up

20
00:02:46,766 --> 00:02:49,326
and talked to God
at the same time.

21
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:55,008
My mother was a very beautiful
and very lonely woman.

22
00:02:55,009 --> 00:02:58,000
She had only known one man,
my father,

23
00:02:58,044 --> 00:03:02,344
and had enjoyed the pleasures
of love for only a few months

24
00:03:02,382 --> 00:03:07,115
and then, gave that all up
for the rest of her life,

25
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:11,556
creating in her
a great sense of frustration.

26
00:03:11,591 --> 00:03:14,424
Her chastity was worse
than that of a virgin.

27
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:16,257
Hijo de puta!

28
00:03:16,296 --> 00:03:18,389
Vete de aquí!

29
00:03:19,566 --> 00:03:21,124
Animal!

30
00:03:34,781 --> 00:03:36,806
Hijo de puta!

31
00:03:42,655 --> 00:03:44,282
Desgraciado!

32
00:03:44,324 --> 00:03:46,918
The most extraordinary
event of my childhood

33
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,019
was provided by the heavens.

34
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:52,054
Water rushed down gutters,

35
00:03:52,098 --> 00:03:55,727
reverberating over
the zinc roof like gunfire

36
00:03:55,768 --> 00:03:58,794
a massive army marching
across the trees,

37
00:03:58,838 --> 00:04:04,401
overflowing, cascading,
thundering into barrels,

38
00:04:04,444 --> 00:04:06,776
a concert of drums,

39
00:04:06,813 --> 00:04:08,747
water falling on water,

40
00:04:08,781 --> 00:04:12,046
drenched and whistling
and out of control,

41
00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:14,246
and under the spell of violence,

42
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:18,992
let loose that would sweep away
almost everything in its path.

43
00:04:18,993 --> 00:04:22,826
Trees, stones,
animals, houses.

44
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:25,921
It was the mystery
of destruction.

45
00:04:25,965 --> 00:04:27,762
The law of life.

46
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,495
As I saw it,

47
00:04:29,535 --> 00:04:31,901
the currents were
roaring my name.

48
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:38,877
Flowers have
reproductive organs.

49
00:04:38,911 --> 00:04:43,780
Class, can anyone
tell us what the male

50
00:04:43,816 --> 00:04:46,876
reproductive organ is called?

51
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:51,886
Reinaldo?

52
00:04:53,092 --> 00:04:54,491
Reinaldo?

53
00:04:54,527 --> 00:04:57,587
A dick.
A long, skinny dick.

54
00:05:05,171 --> 00:05:07,401
Don't ask her where
she comes from.

55
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:10,409
Can't you see she
is from the garden

56
00:05:10,443 --> 00:05:14,038
and the most beautiful
flower of them all?

57
00:05:55,822 --> 00:05:58,154
Buenas tardes,
con permiso.

58
00:05:59,258 --> 00:06:02,250
Señor Fuentes, I didn't mean
to disturb your dinner.

59
00:06:02,295 --> 00:06:03,694
What did he do?

60
00:06:03,730 --> 00:06:06,221
No, he didn't do
anything wrong.

61
00:06:06,265 --> 00:06:10,599
I came here to tell you that
Reinaldo has a special gift.

62
00:06:12,071 --> 00:06:13,561
What special gift?

63
00:06:13,606 --> 00:06:16,404
He has a sensitivity
for poetry.

64
00:07:15,168 --> 00:07:17,227
After that, my grandfather
sold the farm

65
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:20,103
and moved the family
to Holguín,

66
00:07:20,139 --> 00:07:22,266
opened a grocery store,

67
00:07:22,308 --> 00:07:24,538
and refused to speak
to any of us.

68
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:32,880
Holguín was a town
of 200,000 people

69
00:07:32,919 --> 00:07:34,978
and one garbage truck.

70
00:07:56,342 --> 00:07:59,607
The rebels are in Velasco.

71
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:01,545
We can walk it in a day.

72
00:08:01,581 --> 00:08:03,549
Okay.

73
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:05,551
We'll leave tonight.

74
00:08:05,585 --> 00:08:07,018
'Tá bien.

75
00:08:07,053 --> 00:08:10,113
You think you can
do it with her?

76
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:12,522
My name is Reinaldo.
What is yours?

77
00:08:12,558 --> 00:08:13,889
Loly.

78
00:08:13,926 --> 00:08:16,554
- Would you like to dance?
- Cómo no.

79
00:08:35,948 --> 00:08:38,143
¿Qué tú quieres?
Tú eres muy niño.

80
00:08:42,088 --> 00:08:45,023
( radio announcer )
Incorpórate a la lucha.

81
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:50,689
Radio Rebelde, transmitiendo
desde las montañas de Oriente,

82
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:53,221
desde la Sierra Maestra,

83
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:56,235
territorio libre de Cuba.

84
00:08:56,269 --> 00:08:58,396
Aquí Radio Rebelde.

85
00:10:27,026 --> 00:10:28,926
Where are you going, kid?

86
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:31,657
- Up the road.
- Up the road where?

87
00:10:31,697 --> 00:10:32,789
Velasco.

88
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:37,129
Velasco?
You are not from Velasco.

89
00:10:37,169 --> 00:10:41,731
I am from Velasco.
Why do you go to Velasco for?

90
00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:45,232
Ah, the rebels
are in Velasco.

91
00:10:45,277 --> 00:10:47,177
You going to join
the rebels?

92
00:10:47,213 --> 00:10:51,017
Your mamá know you are
going to join the rebels?

93
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:52,484
No.

94
00:10:52,518 --> 00:10:53,712
No.

95
00:10:53,753 --> 00:10:55,277
Where she is?

96
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,482
She's in Miami, working.

97
00:10:57,523 --> 00:11:07,125
Would you like to see?

98
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:11,432
It's upside down.

99
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:13,097
Qué bonita.

100
00:11:18,811 --> 00:11:20,403
You want to hit things?

101
00:11:22,882 --> 00:11:26,579
Sometimes I like
to hit things.

102
00:11:26,619 --> 00:11:31,955
My mother, she has
a store in Velasco.

103
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:35,427
Before that it was my
grandmother's store,

104
00:11:35,461 --> 00:11:38,021
and before that,
it was her mother's store.

105
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:39,759
I have six brothers.

106
00:11:39,799 --> 00:11:43,394
They all want
to join the rebels.

107
00:11:43,436 --> 00:11:46,132
The second one,
he joined the rebels.

108
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:50,632
I'm the middle one,
I don't join the rebels.

109
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,041
( car horn honking )

110
00:11:57,216 --> 00:11:59,047
Get that for me.

111
00:12:11,664 --> 00:12:13,291
Go home.

112
00:12:14,433 --> 00:12:16,663
The rebels are no more
in Velasco.

113
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:18,795
Go on, get off.

114
00:12:18,838 --> 00:12:20,100
Get off!

115
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:23,800
What?
What?

116
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:51,429
Que viva Fidel!

117
00:12:51,470 --> 00:12:53,062
Viva Fidel!

118
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:54,163
Cuba libre!

119
00:15:26,225 --> 00:15:27,692
Translator: Es todo por hoy.

120
00:15:27,726 --> 00:15:29,193
( together )
Spaziva!

121
00:15:49,315 --> 00:15:52,807
As my mother smacked me,
she cursed

122
00:15:52,851 --> 00:15:55,945
and yelled, "Maldito!
Bad seed!"

123
00:15:55,988 --> 00:15:58,513
She shouted at the sky,
"I want to get out of here."

124
00:15:58,557 --> 00:16:01,720
But I really wasn't sure
that's what she wanted.

125
00:16:07,232 --> 00:16:10,668
But now standing over me

126
00:16:10,703 --> 00:16:12,728
she looked like
a huge tree trunk.

127
00:16:13,272 --> 00:16:18,073
And if it didn't hurt so much,
I'd get down on my knees,

128
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:21,273
and ask her to smack me again,
even harder.

129
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:24,809
Then she became beautiful.

130
00:16:24,850 --> 00:16:28,650
How pretty she is in her skirt
made out of a sack

131
00:16:28,687 --> 00:16:31,747
and the blouse she stole
from her sister.

132
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:34,486
I wanted to get up and beg
her forgiveness.

133
00:16:34,526 --> 00:16:39,190
