"Mom, how pretty you are today.

134
00:16:39,231 --> 00:16:40,892
You look like
one of those women

135
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,094
that you can only see
on Christmas cards,"

136
00:16:43,135 --> 00:16:48,038
but I said nothing because
of the the knot in my throat.

137
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:53,769
That was very nice.
What's your name?

138
00:16:53,812 --> 00:16:55,336
Reinaldo Arenas.

139
00:16:55,381 --> 00:16:56,973
Who wrote this?

140
00:16:57,049 --> 00:16:59,483
I did, it's my own--
from my novel.

141
00:16:59,518 --> 00:17:01,213
What do you call this novel?

142
00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:02,914
"Singing from the Well."

143
00:17:02,955 --> 00:17:04,479
Are you a student?

144
00:17:04,523 --> 00:17:08,084
Yes, I'm an agricultural
accountant.

145
00:17:13,332 --> 00:17:15,892
Tell me, do you think
you'd feel at home

146
00:17:15,934 --> 00:17:17,731
working in the national library?

147
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:19,738
The pay won't be very much.

148
00:17:19,772 --> 00:17:22,605
But I can promise you
that you'll have all the books

149
00:17:22,641 --> 00:17:24,438
you could ever hope to read.

150
00:17:24,476 --> 00:17:26,341
I would like that
very much.

151
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:27,777
Thank you very much.

152
00:17:31,784 --> 00:17:32,250
Thank you.

153
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,963
Oye, need a lift?

154
00:17:51,003 --> 00:17:52,527
I want to go down
to Guayanos.

155
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:54,596
Get in.

156
00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:58,209
Hello.

157
00:18:03,315 --> 00:18:05,078
